I loved the Upside-Down Desert.

813
00:34:54,070 --> 00:34:56,050
You know, the...
[stammering]

814
00:34:56,070 --> 00:34:59,150
I can't really picture it,
but, you know, it sounds...

815
00:34:59,170 --> 00:35:02,090
it sounds cool.

816
00:35:05,070 --> 00:35:06,230
I don't know, I can't--
I'm sorry.

817
00:35:06,230 --> 00:35:10,050
I just--I can't...
- Hey. Hey.

818
00:35:11,190 --> 00:35:13,210
- I used to love Fillory
when I was a kid

819
00:35:13,210 --> 00:35:17,050
because I didn't know
what it was.

820
00:35:17,050 --> 00:35:19,050
Plover left out
all of the terrible shit,

821
00:35:19,050 --> 00:35:21,070
and most of the good stuff
he just made up.

822
00:35:21,070 --> 00:35:24,170
Even the fucking Cozy Horse
is a lie.

823
00:35:24,170 --> 00:35:26,010
- Remember what you told me

824
00:35:26,010 --> 00:35:28,010
about letting go
of who you used to be?

825
00:35:28,010 --> 00:35:30,030
- I know, I'm trying.

826
00:35:30,030 --> 00:35:32,150
- Don't.

827
00:35:32,170 --> 00:35:35,110
I don't want you to.

828
00:35:35,110 --> 00:35:38,050
Believing in something--
really believing--

829
00:35:38,070 --> 00:35:40,170
is almost impossible.

830
00:35:40,170 --> 00:35:42,110
[bittersweet music]

831
00:35:42,110 --> 00:35:45,070
But the Quentin I first met...

832
00:35:45,070 --> 00:35:48,010
he believed in magic.

833
00:35:48,030 --> 00:35:50,110
And in Fillory.

834
00:35:50,130 --> 00:35:52,170
- He changed.

835
00:35:52,170 --> 00:35:55,130
He grew up.

836
00:35:55,150 --> 00:35:58,170
- Being an adult doesn't mean
that you have to throw away

837
00:35:58,170 --> 00:36:01,050
what you used to love.

838
00:36:01,070 --> 00:36:04,010
- Then what does it mean?

839
00:36:04,030 --> 00:36:07,070
- Seeing the world
through new eyes.

840
00:36:07,070 --> 00:36:12,000
♪ ♪

841
00:36:12,010 --> 00:36:14,260
And for what it's worth,

842
00:36:14,280 --> 00:36:16,190
the Cozy Horse is real.

843
00:36:16,190 --> 00:36:18,090
I saw it when I was a niffin.

844
00:36:18,110 --> 00:36:20,170
So big you could
build a house on it.

845
00:36:20,170 --> 00:36:22,150
♪ ♪

846
00:36:22,150 --> 00:36:24,230
So...

847
00:36:24,230 --> 00:36:27,070
let's go.

848
00:36:27,070 --> 00:36:34,090
♪ ♪

849
00:36:41,170 --> 00:36:43,210
- [sighs]

850
00:36:44,210 --> 00:36:47,190
Okay, it's just you and me.

851
00:36:49,230 --> 00:36:51,030
You know the worst part

852
00:36:51,050 --> 00:36:53,250
of getting exactly
what you want?

853
00:36:56,090 --> 00:36:58,230
When it's not good enough.

854
00:37:00,260 --> 00:37:03,150
Then what do you do?

855
00:37:05,190 --> 00:37:08,260
If this can't make me happy,
then what would?

856
00:37:13,190 --> 00:37:16,190
Fillory was supposed
to mean something.

857
00:37:17,210 --> 00:37:21,110
I was supposed
to mean something here.

858
00:37:23,150 --> 00:37:25,150
But it's all--it's just--
it's random.

859
00:37:25,150 --> 00:37:26,090
It's so random

860
00:37:26,090 --> 00:37:28,150
that the only way
to save my friends

861
00:37:28,150 --> 00:37:31,090
is to yell at a fucking plant!

862
00:37:34,150 --> 00:37:37,280
Honestly, fuck Fillory
for being so disappointing.

863
00:37:40,090 --> 00:37:41,210
You know what,
maybe I was better off

864
00:37:41,210 --> 00:37:44,110
just believing
that it was fiction.

865
00:37:45,230 --> 00:37:47,280
The idea of Fillory

866
00:37:48,000 --> 00:37:50,190
is what saved my life!

867
00:37:50,190 --> 00:37:52,150
[tense music]

868
00:37:52,170 --> 00:37:54,130
[rueful laugh]

869
00:37:54,130 --> 00:37:57,170
This promise...

870
00:37:57,170 --> 00:38:00,110
that...

871
00:38:00,130 --> 00:38:02,210
people like me...

872
00:38:02,230 --> 00:38:05,280
[weeping]

873
00:38:05,280 --> 00:38:09,070
People like me...
[sniffles]

874
00:38:09,070 --> 00:38:11,230
Can somehow...

875
00:38:11,250 --> 00:38:14,130
♪ ♪

876
00:38:14,130 --> 00:38:16,150
Find an escape.

877
00:38:16,170 --> 00:38:19,230
♪ ♪

878
00:38:19,230 --> 00:38:22,210
There has gotta be
some power in that.

879
00:38:22,210 --> 00:38:25,090
♪ ♪

880
00:38:25,090 --> 00:38:29,230
Shouldn't loving the idea
of Fillory be enough?

881
00:38:29,250 --> 00:38:33,250
♪ ♪

882
00:38:39,170 --> 00:38:42,110
[sighs]

883
00:38:46,130 --> 00:38:49,110
[curious music]

884
00:38:49,130 --> 00:38:55,230
♪ ♪

885
00:38:55,230 --> 00:38:57,260
Guys.

